🌊 ShoreShield — Coastal Hazard Intelligence System

ShoreShield is an AI-assisted coastal hazard intelligence platform designed to detect, analyze, and visualize emerging marine risks using crowdsourced reports and social signal analysis.

The system combines citizen-submitted hazard reports with AI-driven event interpretation to identify potential coastal threats such as rough seas, flooding, pollution events, abnormal wave activity, and other ocean-related hazards. Instead of treating reports as isolated incidents, ShoreShield performs event fusion by correlating reports spatially and temporally to detect meaningful risk clusters.

Key capabilities include:

• Crowdsourced hazard reporting with geolocation support
• AI-powered hazard classification and severity estimation
• Social signal integration for multi-source validation
• Spatial clustering using geospatial distance analysis
• Temporal grouping of related hazard events
• Confidence-ranked alert generation using source diversity, recency, and report density
• Explainable operational intelligence feed for real-time monitoring
• Geospatial visualization of clustered coastal risks

The platform uses zero-shot NLP via Anthropic API to extract hazard type, severity, confidence, and inferred location information from unstructured reports. A custom confidence engine combines AI certainty, source diversity, temporal recency, and correlated report volume to prioritize alerts and reduce false positives.

Unlike traditional dashboard-focused systems, ShoreShield emphasizes interpretable hazard intelligence and early event detection through multi-source coastal signal fusion.

Tech Stack:
• Next.js
• TypeScript
• Firebase Firestore
• MapLibre GL
• Anthropic API
• OpenStreetMap
